Rizal Returned To Manila : June 26,1892 Declared as an enemy of the state because of his novels La Liga Filipina - a social reformist group advocating social reform through legal means, (Spanish authorities which led to Rizals arrest on "JULY 6,1892" Gov. Gen. Eulogio Despujol - ordered the arrest as a political move to appease the fairs. He published in Graceta de Manila (the grounds for Rizals arrest) ( anti catholic and anti-friar stance) Rizal's life in Dapitan from 1892 to 1896 WINS LOTTERY IN MANILA September 21,1892- (together with Ricardo Carnicero and another Spaniard) His share amounted to 6,200 pesos Purchased land approximately one kilometer away from Dapitan in a place know as Talisay Lottery is the vice of Jose Rizal "This was his only vice" said the Spaniard biographer Wenceslao E. Retana August 1893 - members of his family took turns in visiting him -among them were his mother, sisters Trinidad, maria, narcissa, and nephews teodisio, estanislao ,Mauricio and prudencio December 19, 1893- describe his life in Dapitan with his letter to Bluementrit Rizal practiced medicine in DAPITAN Rizals fame as a physician particularly "eye specialist" pave way to patients from different part of pH from " Luzon Bohol, Cebu, Panay negros, and Mindanao and even Hong Kong" He spent many months in draining the marshes in order to get rid of MALARIA that Infested in Dapitan. Also help people putting lamp post at every corner of the town "COCONUT OIL LAMPS" He made an big relief maps of Mindanao in the plaza used to teach Geography ART WORKS IN DAPITAN He contributed his painting skills to the sisters of charity preparing sanctuary of the Holy Virgin in their private chapel SCULPTURE WORKS OF RIZAL *The mothes revenge *the Dapitan girl *woodcarving of Josephine Bracken *bust of st. Paul which he gave to father Pastels CONTRIBUTION TO SCIENCE Four-year exile in Dapitan Rizal built up a rich collection of conchology which consisted of 346 shells representing 203 species. Rare specimens were discovered and named after him . Among these were *DRACO RIZALI *APOGONIA RIZALI *RHACOPHORUS RIZALI RIZAL AS AN EDUCATOR Established a school for boys in 1983 existed until the of his exile July 1896 Pupils did not pay any tuition instead of charging them , he made them work in his garden, fields , and construction projects in the community Rizal thought these boys ready, writing languages (Spanish and English) , Geography, mathematics arithmetic and geometry, industrial work nature, morals and gymnastics Outside the class hours, Rizal encourages play had boxing, wrestling, Stone-throwing, swimming, Arnis, (native fencing) , and boating WATER SYSTEM FOR DAPITAN Held title of expert surveyor (perito agrimensor) obtained from ateneo . LINGUISTIC STUDIES April 5, 1896 - his first year of exile in Dapitan, he wrote to BLUEMENTRITT He knew 22 languages as follows: Tagalog, ilocano, bisayan,subanon, Latin, Greek, English, Hebrew, Sanskrit, dutch, Catalan, Italian, Chinese, japanese, Portuguese, swedish, and Russian RIZAL AS A FARMER Brought 16 hectares of land in Talisay, built his home, school, and hospital and planted cacao, coffee, sugarcane, coconuts and fruits trees, total holding reach 70 hectares containing 6,000 hemp plants , 1000 coconut trees a d numerous fruit trees, sugarcane, corn z cogfyand cacao He introduced modern agricultural methods to Dapitan farmers, imported agricultural machinery from the United States RIZAL'S INVENTION Invented a wooden machine for making bricks this machine could make 6000 bricks daily 1887 while practicing medicine in Calamba, he invented cigarettes lighter which he sent to BLUEMENTRITT called it "sulpukan" made wood and it's mechanism is based on the principle of compressed air RIZAL AND JOSEPHINE BRACKEN Having heard of Rizals fame as an ophthalmologist, George Traufer who was suffering from eye ailment traveled from Hong Kong to Dapitan . He was accompanied by his adopted daughter, Josephine bracken who eventually fell inlove with Rizal

"NETWORKING 2 STUDY NOTES" A NETWORK is A set of devices(often reffered to as nodes) connected by communication links. USES OF COMPUTER NETWORKS Bussiness- E-commerce, Email, Resource Sharing Home- Personal use, Person to Person to Person Communications Mobile- Mobile Phones NETWORK CRITERIA -a network must be able to meet certain number of criteria. Performance - Can be measured by transit time and response time. Reliability - Is measured by the frequency of failures Security - This refers to the ability to protect data from unauthorized access. DATA COMMUNICATION - Is the active process of transporting data from one point to another. The term TELECOMMUNICATION means communication at a DISTANCE. FIVE COMPONENTS OF DATA COMMUNICATION Transmitter - the device that sends the message. Receiver - the device that receives the message. Medium - the physical path by which a message travels from sender to receiver. Message - the transmission (data) to be communicated. Protocol - set of rules that governs data communication. DATA REPRESENTATION - Anything that can have two different states can represent anything on a digital device. DATA FLOW - The route between origin, via nodes, to a destination taken by a packet of data. 3 WAYS TO TRANSMIT DATA Simplex - uses one circuit in one direction only such as in radio or TV transmission. Half-duplex (HDX) - one way transmission and it also use only one circuit as simplex does but it is used in both directions. Full-duplex (FDX) - two-way transmission but it uses two circuits for communication. THE INTERNET - a global computer network providing a variety of information and communication facilities, consisting of interconnected networks using standardized communication protocols. The first network launched by the US Defense Department was called ARPANET Originally the man who came up with this idea of networking by computers was JCR LICKLIDER Advanced Research Projects Agency Network (ARPANET) HTTP - Hyper Text Transfer Protocol is a system that transfers data from one machine to another. HTTPS - Hyper Text Transfer Protocol Secure is the same thing as HTTP, but it is secure, meaning the data sent from one machine to another is encrypted. WWW - World Wide Web , combination of all resources and users on the Internet that are using the Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP). WWW also simply called subdomain URL- stands for UNIFORM RESOURCE LOCATOR. A URL is nothing more than the address of a given unique resource on the Web. Domain- A domain is what you type in to tell the machine where to get data from, a domain is in the format of 'subdomain.domain. extention' sorta like '
www.google.com
.' So when you type in google.com, the machine looks that up and finds that the server for 
http://google.com
   SubDomain - A subdomain allows the domain to have multiple places to get data from but only using one domain.   Protocols - is the special set of rules that end points in a telecommunication connection use when they communicate.

"CONTINUATION OF NETWORKING 2 STUDY NOTES" NETWORK PROTOCOL - are a set of rules outling how connected devices communicate across a network to exchange information easily and safety. COMMON INTERNET PROTOCOL Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP). Transmission Control Protocol / Internet (TCP/IP). User Datagram Protocol/Internet protocol (UDP/IP). File Transfer Protocol (FTP). Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCP). Spanning Tree Protocol (STP). Secure Shell (SSH) SSH File Transfer Protocol (SFTP). Key Element of Protocol Syntax : syntax refers to the structure or the format of the data that gets exchanged between the devices. Semantics : Semantics defines data transmitted between devices. Timing : Timing refers to the synchronization and coordination between devices while transferring the data. Sequence control : Sequence control ensures the proper ordering of data packets. Flow Control : Flow control regulates device data delivery. Error Control : Error control mechanisms detect and fix data transmission faults. Security : Network security safeguards data confidentiality, integrity, and authenticity. STANDARDS - Standards are the set of rules for data communication that are needed for exchange of information among devices. TYPES OF STANDARDS De Jure Standard. : The meaning of the word De Jure is By Law or By Regulations. De Facto Standard : The meaning of the work De Facto is By Fact or By Convention . TYPES OF PROTOCOL Network Layer Protocols : Network layer protocols operate in the network layer which is also known as the Layer 3 of the network architecture. Transport layer Protocols : Transport layer protocols works in transport layer which provides end-to-end service Application Layer Protocol : Application layer protocol working in the application layer of the network Wireless Protocols : Wireless protocols basically used in wireless communication which enables data transfer Routing Protocols : Routing protocol establishes the best/optimal network pathways Security Protocols : security protocol protects data confidentiality, integrity, and authenticity Internet Protocols : IP identifies devices uniquely. Internet protocol provides data communication A STANDARD ORGANIZATION, STANDARDS BODY, STANDARD DEVELOPING ORGANIZATION, (SDO) OR STANDARD SETTING ORGANIZATION (SSO) is an organization whose primary activities are developing, c9rdinating, promulgating, revising, amending, reissuing, interpreting, or other wise producing technical standard. NETWORK TOPOLOGY is the arrangement of a network, including its nodes and connecting lines. There are two ways of defining network geometry: the PHYSICAL TOPOLOGY and the LOGICAL (OR SIGNAL) TOPOLOGY. BUS TOPOLOGY is a network type in which every computer and network device is connected to single cable. RING TOPOLOGY because it forms a ring as each computer is connected to another computer, with the last one connected to the first. STAR TOPOLOGY In this type of topology all the computers are connected to a single hub through a cable. MESH TOPOLOGY mesh network, devices are connected with many redundant interconnections between network nodes. TREE TOPOLOGY has a root node and all other nodes are connected to it forming a hierarchy. It is also called hierarchical topology. HYBRID TOPOLOGY two different types of topologies which is a mixture of two or more topologies.
